Question 4- Create a function called HourOfDay() that takes one argument which is a textual representation of a timestamp in the format YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS and uses a regular expression to extract the hour (or you can use the lubridate package to extract the hour). For example, the function should take a timestamp in the following format: 2020-02-01 11:10:25 and return 11

#Creating function
HourOfDay <- function(timestamp= "2020-08-01 11:18:56")
{
  date_input <- ymd_hms(timestamp)
hour_day <- hour(date_input)
return(hour_day)
}

#Applying function
HourOfDay("2020-02-01 11:10:25")
## [1] 11
# One can try writing multiple dates with yyyy-hh-mm hh:mm:ss format and the created function will return the extracted hour

Question 6- Report the median trip distance grouped by the lpep_pickup_hour. Visualize the results and explain any patterns you observed based on the hour of day.

#Using mutate to extract hour from the pick up datetime and then calculating trip duration.
ans_6 <- tripdata_df %>%
  mutate(hour_trip_start = factor(hour(lpep_pickup_datetime)),
  trip.duration= as.numeric(difftime(lpep_dropoff_datetime,lpep_pickup_datetime,units="mins"))) %>%
  group_by(hour_trip_start)
#Excluding median, calculating frequency of trips based on pick up hour. Maximum pickups are during the evening hours, probably due to office closing hours
ggplot(data= ans_6) +
  geom_bar(aes (x= hour_trip_start))

#To calculate median trip distance based on pick up hour
ans_6 %>%
  group_by(hour_trip_start) %>%
  summarise(med.TD= median(trip.duration)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x= hour_trip_start, y= med.TD))+
  geom_point() +
  geom_line(aes (group=1), linetype= "dotted")+
  labs(x='Pickup hour',
       y='Median Trip Duration in Mins',
       title='Median Trip Duration by Pickup hour of day')

# Explanation- The maximum median trip duration is for pick ups that occur at 6am. This would either mean that the duration increases for rides starting at 6 am due to an increased amount of traffic as those are early morning office hours. It can also be due to people travelling early in the morning to reach a destination that is farther off. The next peak is at 15 hours with a median duration of ~13.75 and it decreases toward the end of the day as either the roads are empty or people only travel short distances.
